---
title: Object field
---
The `object` field lets you structure complex object schemas that can contain any other field types.

## Usage example

Simple:

```typescript
snapshot: fields.object({
  name: fields.text({ label: 'Name' }),
  age: fields.integer({ label: 'Age' }),
})
```

Complex:

```typescript
snapshot: fields.object({
  name: fields.text({ label: 'Name' }),
  age: fields.integer({ label: 'Age' }),

  // Nested relationship array
  projects: fields.array(
    fields.relationship({
      label: 'Projects',
      collection: 'projects',
      validation: {
        isRequired: true,
      },
    }),
    {
      label: 'Projects',
      itemLabel: (props) => props.value ?? 'Please select a project',
    }
  ),
})
```

## Type signature

```typescript
object<Fields extends Record<string, ComponentSchema>>(fields: Fields)
```
